<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" data-id="23614" src="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/frost-1024x683.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-23614" srcset="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/frost-1024x683.jpeg 1024w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/frost-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/frost-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/frost-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Frost Library at Glendon Campus</figcaption></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="678" data-id="23616" src="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Screenshot-2023-02-27-at-11.21.44-AM-1024x678.png" alt="" class="wp-image-23616" srcset="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Screenshot-2023-02-27-at-11.21.44-AM-1024x678.png 1024w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Screenshot-2023-02-27-at-11.21.44-AM-300x199.png 300w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Screenshot-2023-02-27-at-11.21.44-AM.png 1097w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Group Study rooms</figcaption></figure>
</figure>



<div style="height:0px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p></p>



<p>Whether you come to York U libraries to work or study, finding the right spot is key.  Need to work with a partner or a group or just need some quiet space? No problem. Whether you study best in silence or in study nook with groups, our libraries have you covered. From Scott Library near Central Square to Bronfman Library at Schulich, to Steacie Library in the Science building and on Glendon campus with the scenic views at Frost, there are plenty of study spaces for all your needs. We asked our students to share their favourite spots. Our York U Libraries' peer mentor students, Taylor Wulf, Mila Sushkova, Musaddiq Ahmed, Timi Akinbaleye, Guillaume Jean and Subhay Anwar, share their favourite study areas. </p>



<p>Here’s what they had to say:</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best place to get serious studying done</h2>



<p><strong>Taylor:</strong> If I need to get some serious studying done for finals, I like to go to Bronfman library on the 2nd floor because it is a quiet space and I'm able to get a lot done there.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-01-at-11.13.28-AM.png"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="678" src="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-01-at-11.13.28-AM-1024x678.png" alt="phot of Bronfman library study space" class="wp-image-23740" srcset="https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-01-at-11.13.28-AM-1024x678.png 1024w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-01-at-11.13.28-AM-300x199.png 300w, https://www.library.yorku.ca/web/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Screenshot-2023-03-01-at-11.13.28-AM.png 1095w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Bronfman Library</figcaption></figure>



<p><strong>Musaddiq:</strong> 4th / 5th floors of Scott Library. The pin drop silence with practically zero distractions, helps me get my stuff done with full focus</p>



<p><strong>Timi:</strong> My favourite study space during exams is Steacie because it is very quiet during exam time.</p>



<p><strong>Guillaume:</strong> At Frost, I like the individual study stations along the windows on the second floor. The partitions provide some privacy that block any distractions while having a stunning view of the manor and the rose garden.</p>



<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-28 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
